leads.lead_text: Usually suckering shrubs; phyllodes 1.5–2.5 mm wide, mostly acute at apex (ignoring terminal mucro if present), margin not or indistinctly indented around gland; young growth not or lightly pruinose; native to upper reaches of the Snowy River and nearby areas, sometimes naturalised outside this region.

Non-suckering shrubs; phyllodes 2.5–5 mm wide, obtuse or rounded at apex (ignoring terminal mucro if present), margin usually distinctly indented around gland; at least younger stems and phyllodes usually distinctly pruinose; known only from near Mt Typo in north-east Victoria
